    "more": "<p><strong>OpenAlex Domain, Fields and Subfields</strong></p><p><a href='images/Logo YUFE-General.png' target='_blank' rel='noopener'><img src='images/Logo YUFE-General.png' alt='Logo YUFE' style='max-width:100%;height:auto;'></a></p><p><a href='images/OPENLEX_1.jpg' target='_blank' rel='noopener'><img src='images/OPENALEX_1.jpg' alt='OpenAlex Fields and Subfields_1' style='max-width:100%;height:auto;'></a></p><p><a href='images/OPENALEX_2.jpg' target='_blank' rel='noopener'><img src='images/OPENALEX_2.jpg' alt='OpenAlex Fields and Subfields_2' style='max-width:100%;height:auto;'></a></p><p><a href='images/OPENALEX_3.jpg' target='_blank' rel='noopener'><img src='images/OPENALEX_3.jpg' alt='OpenAlex Fields and Subfields 3' style='max-width:100%;height:auto;'></a></p>",
    "intro": "\u003cp\u003e  \nThis interactive graph represents the hierarchical structure of research interests in \n\u003cstrong\u003ePhysical Sciences\u003c/strong\u003e extracted from a set of responses to the YUFE Task 5.3 survey. Following the classification avilable in <a href='http://www.openalex.org' target='_blank'> </a>, the 3 levels displayed are: \n\u003cul\u003e  \n  \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan style\u003d\"color:#24EB84;\"\u003eDomain\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e  \n  \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan style\u003d\"color:#EB3424;\"\u003eField\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e  \n  \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan style\u003d\"color:#2563EB;\"\u003eSubfield\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\nThe size of each node is proportional to the number of mentions (\u003cem\u003eWeight\u003c/em\u003e) received from the participants in the survey. \nUse the search box or the group selector to focus on specific areas. \n\u003c/p\u003e  ",
    "title": "Network Physical Sciences "
  },
